esqlQuery.esql:
// Alert when Kubernetes nodes report network unavailable status.
//
// What triggers this alert:
// Node network interface marked as unavailable — no pod networking possible.
//
// Common causes:
// CNI plugin failure, network interface down, cloud provider networking issues.
//
// Action needed:
// Check node network configuration, CNI plugin status, and cloud provider networking.
//
// To scope to a cluster, add: AND `orchestrator.cluster.name` == "YOUR_CLUSTER"
TS metrics-kubernetes.node-*
| WHERE `kubernetes.node.status.network_unavailable` == "true"
| STATS doc_count = COUNT(*)
  BY `orchestrator.cluster.name`, `kubernetes.node.name`
| WHERE doc_count > 0
